         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">30/8/78. ¶  ¶ I have been on the sickbed for three weeks, dear Mr Buchanan, ¶  and am still so very enfeebled that I cannot write at length. Pray do  ¶ not ¶  trouble about the sections of the fern tr...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">78.08.30</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John Buchanan</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A644, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">30/8/78.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have been on the sickbed for three weeks, dear Mr Buchanan,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">John Buchanan (1819-1898).</p>
               </note> and am still so very enfeebled that I cannot write at length. Pray do <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not</hi>
               </seg> trouble about the sections of the fern trees, unless quite handy. I do not wish to involve you in trouble &amp; expense; I really have no claims on your goodness. Can you procure the showy floating water plant with comparatively large white flowers of your northern rivers? Mr Kirk sent me a flower many years ago, but no leaves. He must have got it from some settler.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful remembrance</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">real</hi>
               </seg>
               <name key="Zannichellia%20palustris">Zannichellia palustris</name> now also from Australia; so you may have it there as well,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">New Zealand.</p>
               </note> though you seem to have <name key="Lepilaena">Lepilaena</name> also.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Lepilaena">Lepilaena</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Zannichellia%20palustris">Zannichellia palustris</name>
            </p>
         </div>
